<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11629] Operational concerns for Replication should call out ZooKeeper</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11629</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book/developing.html#design.invariants.zk.data&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;design invariants state that ZooKeeper data is safe to delete&lt;/a&gt;. However, &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/replication.html#Replication_Zookeeper_State&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;replication only stores its data in zookeeper&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
This can lead to operators accidentally disabling their replication set up while attempting to recover from an unrelated issue by clearing the zk state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should update the &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book/cluster_replication.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;operational concerns section on replication&lt;/a&gt; to call out that the /hbase/replication tree should not be deleted. We should probably also add a warning to the set up steps.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
